    "summary": "I believe that privacy & security are essential drivers of guarantying the wellbeing of customers and employees of organizations. Besides that privacy is a fundamental right, organizations should have the ethical way of thinking and acting embedded in their DNA. \n\nEmbedding privacy compliance structurally in your organization means that people, process and systems have to be aligned with each other, guided by a clear and effective governance. Strategy and vision should be focused on processing (personal) data from an ethical perspective, not about what legally might be possible. This safeguards the trust of your employees and customers.\n\nMy skills are designing and implementing the successful mix of privacy requirements needed to change organizations. This change starts with bringing important stakeholders from marketing, legal, IT and management together and make them aware of the importance. As a former marketeer I do understand the value that data can have for data intensive organizations. Whit this as an valuable experience, I assure that key elements like privacy by design & default, training and awareness programs, assessments and auditing, data subject rights, legal grounds and data retention are being well embedded in the organization.\n\nAs a privacy professional, I see myself as a specialist with a natural habit of seeking challenges in complex environments. I like to share my knowledge, inspire people and get my daily energy by working in a committed and fun team. I am not afraid to speak out and love the diversion of working with executives, managers and operational colleagues.\n\nI do not believe in \u201cI have nothing to hide\u201d, instead I think we have a lot to protect simply by the fact we cannot predict what the power of information will be in the future. Ostensibly innocent personal data of today can turn out to be one of the lethal weapons of tomorrow. This we have seen in history.\n",
